<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN248-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇai, atu; tuṟai, tāpatanilai.
      <gap quantity="3" reason="lost" unit="character"/>ekkūr (Cām.-1v: okkūr) 
      mācāttaṉār pāṭiyatu.
       <app>
        <lem wit="#C8">kuruntalar kaṇṇi</lem>
        <rdg wit="#C3">kurunakar</rdg>
        <rdg wit="#C2"><space quantity="3" unit="character"/>ru nakar</rdg>
      </app>
     koḻunaṉ māynteṉak karuntaṭaṅ kaṇṇi kaimmai 
     <app>
      <lem wit="#C8">kūṟiṉṟu</lem>
      <rdg wit="#C2 #C3">kūṟiyatu</rdg>
     </app>.        
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN248">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>aḷiya tāmē ciṟuveḷ ḷāmpa</l>
<l>liḷaiya mākat taḻaiyā yiṉavē</l>
<l>yiṉiyē,</l>
<l>peruvaḷak koḻunaṉ māynteṉap poḻutumaṟut</l>
<l>tiṉṉā vaika luṇṇu</l>
<l>mallip paṭūum pullā yiṉavē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>  Pitiful [are] they, the small white waterlilies.</l>
<l>When we were young, they were foliage [for a skirt].</l>
<l>Now, </l>
<l>since [our] great prosperous husband is gone, defying the time</l>
<l>they have become the grass that provides the seeds</l>
<l>that are eaten in pleasureless days.</l>
</lg>
    </div>
  </body>
